
---
import Weather from './Weather.astro';
---

<div id="container">
  <main>
	<link rel="stylesheet" href="/src/styles/global.css" />
    <!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Welcome to Arcadia Bay</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Pacifico&family=Roboto:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

</head>
<body>
    <header>
		<a href="/" class="logo">
        <img src="/src/ab/Prescott-foundation.png" alt="Prescott Foundation">
		<img src="/src/ab/blackwell.jpg" alt="Blackwell Academy">
		<img src="/src/ab/TwoWhalesDiner logo.png" alt="Two Whales Dinner">
		<img src="/src/ab/BeanHipCafeLeaflet.jpg" alt="BeanHipCafe">
		<img src="/src/ab/Typhon mining HS.png" alt="Typhon Mining">
    	</a>

        <h1>Welcome to Arcadia Bay</h1>
        <p>Discover Arcadia Bay – Nature, Culture, Adventure</p>
		<div class="social-links">
        <a href="https://reddit.com/r/lifeisstrange" target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label="LifeIsStrange Reddit">
            <img src="/src/ab/reddit.png" alt="Reddit">
        </a>
        <a href="discord.gg/twowhalesdiner" target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label="TwoWhalesDiner Discord">
            <img src="/src/ab//discord.png" alt="Discord">
        </a>
        <a href="https://www.facebook.com/DONTNOD.Entertainment" target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label="DONTNOD Facebook">
            <img src="/src/ab/facebook.png" alt="Facebook">
        </a>
		
    </div>
</header>

    <nav>
        <a href="#about">Our Town</a>
		<a href="#newsevents">Events / News</a>
		<a href="#explore">Explore Arcadia Bay</a>
        <a href="#gallery">Gallery</a>
        <a href="#contact">Contact</a>
    </nav>

    <div class="hero">
        <div class="hero-text">
            <h2>Where Every Choice Matters</h2>
            <p>Embrace the beauty and secrets of Arcadia Bay</p>
			
        </div>
    </div>
	

    <section id="about">
        <h3>About Arcadia Bay</h3>
        <p style="text-align:center; max-width:700px; margin:auto; color:#dcd6f7;">
            Arcadia Bay is a picturesque coastal town full of charm, history, and mystery. Explore its hidden corners, connect with its people, and uncover the choices that shape its story.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section id="places">
        <h3>Popular Places</h3>
        <div class="info-cards">
            <div class="card">
                <img src="/src/ab/oldblackwell.webp" alt="Blackwell Academy">
                <h4>Blackwell Academy</h4>
                <p>The iconic school where students learn, create, and sometimes find themselves in unexpected situations.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <img src="/src/ab/Arcadiagas.webp" alt="Arcadia Gas">
                <h4>ArcadiaGas</h4>
                <p>Arrive in the late afternoon for a scenic sunset while refueling. The lighthouse is just a 10-minute drive north!</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <img src="/src/ab/overlookpark.webp" alt="Culmination State Park">
                <h4>Culmination State Park</h4>
                <p>Culmination Peak, renamed Culmination State Park, was designated as a state park in 1997 by order of Governor John Kitzhaber. </p>
            </div>
			<div class="card">
                <img src="/src/ab/lighthouse.webp" alt="Arcadia Bay Lighthouse">
                <h4>Arcadia Bay Lighthouse</h4>
                <p>The must‑see landmark for sunset views and coastal photography.</p>
            </div>
			<div class="card">
                <img src="/src/ab/ArcadiaBayBeach.png" alt="The Beach & Harbor">
                <h4>The Beach & Harbor</h4>
                <p>Walkable coastline with scenic views; ideal for picnics, sea breezes, and whale watching.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="gallery">
        <h3><br>Gallery</h3>
        <p style="text-align:center; max-width:700px; margin:auto; color:#dcd6f7;">
            Snapshots of Arcadia Bay – from foggy mornings to colorful sunsets.
        </p>
        <div class="info-cards">
            <div class="card"><img src="/src/ab/ABSIGN.png" alt="Sunset"></div>
            <div class="card"><img src="/src/ab/forest.jpg" alt="Forest"></div>
            <div class="card"><img src="/src/ab/LiS1-Tobanga-2.webp" alt="Street"></div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="contact">
        <h3>Contact</h3>
        <p style="text-align:center; max-width:700px; margin:auto; color:#dcd6f7;">
            Want to learn more about Arcadia Bay or share your own story?
			You can contact us directly at: info@arcadiabay.org
		</p>
        
    </section>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2026 Arcadia Bay. All rights reserved.</p>
		<small>Created and hosted by <a href="https://melbyeit.dk">MelbyeDev</a></small>
    </footer>

</body>
</html>
  </main>